        <div class="rp-title">Why You're Losing Muscle After 40 (And It's Not Your Workout) →</div>
      </div>
      <span class="rp-arrow">→</span>
    </a>

    <h2>Your Per-Meal Target by Bodyweight</h2>

    <p>
      The research-supported per-meal threshold is approximately <strong>0.24 grams of protein per pound of body weight</strong>. That's the amount needed to maximally stimulate muscle protein synthesis in older adults. Here's what that looks like in practice:
    </p>

    <div class="weight-table">
      <div class="wt-label">Per-meal protein targets</div>
      <div class="wt-headline">How Much Per Meal at Your Bodyweight</div>

      <div class="wt-row">
        <div class="wt-weight">150 lbs</div>
        <div class="wt-target">~36g per meal</div>
        <div class="wt-daily">~108–144g daily</div>
      </div>
